      &lt;img alt="Photo illustration of Elon Musk surrounded by raining dollar bills." src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/L_xdLK4R7iLUF4RWKJMIhRolFMw=/20x0:2021x1334/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73683843/STK022_ELON_MUSK_CVIRGINIA_E.0.jpg" /&gt;
        &lt;figcaption&gt;Image: Cath Virginia / The Verge, Getty Images&lt;/figcaption&gt;
    &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;p id="rAu6vV"&gt;Philadelphia District Attorney Larry Krasner is suing Elon Musk and his Donald Trump-supporting America PAC. Filed Monday in Philadelphia Common Pleas Court, it’s the first legal action against &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/20/24274971/elon-musk-1-million-prize-america-pac-petition-voting-presidential-election"&gt;Musk’s $1 million daily award offered to registered voters&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
